@sijie It is not. Still have `java.lang.RuntimeException: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.pulsar.functions.runtime.shaded.org.glassfish.jersey.client.JerseyClientBuilder`. You can reproduce using createTenant method from function body:

```java
import javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder;
import javax.ws.rs.client.Entity;
import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;
import javax.ws.rs.core.Response;

import org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64;

import org.glassfish.jersey.client.authentication.HttpAuthenticationFeature;
import org.glassfish.jersey.client.ClientConfig;
import org.glassfish.jersey.logging.LoggingFeature;

public class PulsarRESTAPIUtils {
  public final static String PULSAR_REST_API_URL = "pulsarurl";
  public final static String PULSAR_AUTH_STRING = "token";

  public static void createTenant(String tenant) throws Exception {
    String path = new StringBuilder("tenants/").append(tenant).toString();

    Response response = ClientBuilder
      .newClient()
      .target(new StringBuilder(PULSAR_REST_API_URL).append(path).toString())
      .request()
      .header("Content-Type", "application/json")
      .header("Authorization", new StringBuilder("Bearer ").append(PULSAR_AUTH_STRING).toString())
      .put(Entity.json(""));

    if (response.getStatus() < 200 && response.getStatus() > 299) {
      throw new Exception(String.format("%d on creation of tenant %s", response.getStatus(), tenant));
    }
  }
}
```

But is `org.glassfish.jersey.client` shaded, and it changes nothing that this method comes from static context?

@jiazhai 
>> There are some PRs on going for PIP-36, will it partly solve this issue?

No, right now, pulsar can only support up to 5MB message size and PIP-36 doesn't support large message but it allows broker to configure max message size from 0 to 5MB. we need it for customers who want to publish large message into large-scale specialized pulsar instance for which txn might not be feasible option. it's similar like chunking in kafka mentioned [here](https://medium.com/workday-engineering/large-message-handling-with-kafka-chunking-vs-external-store-33b0fc4ccf14).
